Title: the red dust gets into your heart
DateModified: '2019-02-01'
DatePublished: '2019-02-01'
Url: https://www.worldnomads.com/create/scholarships/writing/2019/applications/the-red-dust-gets-into-your-heart
SetInCountry: Kenya
Category: A leap into the unknown
AuthorName: kevin mann
AuthorCountry: United States of America
Text: 'what happens when a group of surburban long islanders travel to kenya to work
  with a group of orphans?since 2001 the dance of friendship has coninued with a variety
  of different dance partners.since the jerusha mwiraria hope children''s fund home
  opened in 2005 a marvelous relationship has evolved.from 18 youth in 2005 to 96
  today the success stories continue.

  risper mwendwa came to the home in 2005.she was a primary student from isiolo who
  was brought to the home by her 16 year old sister.she finished primary classes at
  gikumene primary.risper scored 308 on her KCPE examination.she completed her secondary
  studies at yururu secondary boarding school.next stop meru national polytechic for
  human relations and business adminstration.risper completed her studies in december
  of 2018.soon to be 24 risper represents the best the orphnge can hope for.for orphan
  at 11 to college graduate at 23.risper turns 24 on 2/28/19.

  more vignettes and stories to follow.'
